PART I: POWER SUMS в†’ ELEMENTARY SYMMETRIC FUNCTIONS
========================================================================

For eigenvalues О»в‚Ѓ, ..., О»_{p-1} (excluding О»в‚Ђ = m):
  p_k = ОЈ О»_j^k  (power sums)
  e_k = ОЈ_{|I|=k} О _{jв€€I} О»_j  (elementary symmetric)

Newton's identities connect them:
  kВ·e_k = ОЈ_{i=1}^{k} (-1)^{i-1} p_i В· e_{k-i}

For the REAL MAGNITUDES x_j = |О»_j|ВІ (since we care about magnitudes):
  s_k = ОЈ x_j^k / (ОЈ x_j)^k = normalized power sum
  E_k = e_k(xв‚Ѓ,...,x_{p-1}) / (ОЈ x_j)^k = normalized elementary symmetric

The IPR = s_2 / s_1ВІ = (1/(p-1)) В· PR^{-1}
  For Paley: s_2/s_1ВІ = 1/(p-1) в†’ IPR = 1/(p-1), PR = p-1
  For Interval: s_2/s_1ВІ в‰€ 1/3 в†’ IPR в‰€ 1/3, PR в‰€ 3

The cycle count involves COMPLEX eigenvalues, not just magnitudes.
But the KEY ratio is s_k(magnitudes) vs actual trace formula.


